Package: swaylock-plugin
Architecture: linux-any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 python3,
Description: screen locker for Wayland compositors with animated backgrounds
 swaylock-plugin is a fork of swaylock, a screen locking utility for
 Wayland compositors. It can display the animated output of any wallpaper
 program that implements the wlr-layer-shell-unstable-v1 protocol as the
 lockscreen background: run `swaylock-plugin --command 'my-wallpaper ...'`.
 .
 The package ships the swaylock-plugin locker, the swaylock-sleep-watcher
 helper (ends the unlocked grace period when the system suspends), PAM
 configuration, a man page, shell completions, and an example Xwayland
 wrapper for running X11 wallpaper programs through windowtolayer.
